def substrcount(str, substr):
    count = 0
    for i in range(len(str) - len(substr) + 1):
        if str[i:i+len(substr)] == substr:
            count += 1
    return count

answer:
```javascript
function substrcount(str, substr) {
  var count = 0;
  for (var i = 0; i < str.length - substr.length + 1; i++) {
    if (str.substring(i, i + substr.length) === substr) {
      count++;
    }
  }
  return count;
}
```

